[Rajasthan is the largest state of the Republic of India in terms of area
but encompasses most of the area of the large, inhospitable Great Indian
Desert (Thar Desert), which has an edge that parallels the Sutlej-Indus
river valley along its border with Pakistan. The region borders Pakistan to
the west, Gujarat to the south west, Madhya Pradesh to the south east,
Uttar Pradesh and Haryana to the north east, and Punjab to the north. It
can be found on the map at <http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rajasthan>. - Mod.LL]
